@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Whippo' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  You play by clicking on any tile located at the left or right
half part of the game board. This will move all tiles located on
the same row by one position toward the left or right, respectively.
A tile located at the right or left edge of the game board will go
to the other edge...

  However, if the clicked tile is located over or under the empty
space, it will move toward up or down towards the empty space.

  Tiles can be placed so the lowest or highest number of bars are
placed at the top of the game board, as long as all the numbers of
bars increase (or decrease) by one unit downward, and are of the
same colour in each column.

  You can change the game board size by clicking on the triangular
shaped tiles located at the right of the game board. The tiles with
'+' signs increase the size of the board in the direction their
shape indicate and the tiles with the '-' signs do the opposite.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the 'New Game'
button.

  Have fun!

@endnode

